        <item>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Cell Location Privacy Act of 2017</b> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to make it a crime to knowingly use a cell-site simulator. A violator is subject to a fine, a prison term of up to 10 years, or both. <p>The bill creates exceptions to allow a governmental entity to use a cell-site simulator in certain circumstances&#8212;pursuant to a warrant, to conduct electronic surveillance under the Foreign Intelligence Service Act of 1978, or in an emergency situation. <p>It prohibits the use of information unlawfully acquired from a cell-site simulator as evidence in a legal or official proceeding.]]></text>
